<H6>To describe someone's height you can say that the are tall or short.Tall People are higher than short people.Someone who is thin and tall call be called lanky.To say someone is short and also small you can say that they are petite.If you are talking about a child they may be pint sized.

Someone who weighs more than average can be curvy well-built full-bodied or heavy.(Curvy is usualy only used to describe women.) You might also say
someone has some meat on their bones.This is a casual way of saying they are overweight and it might rude to someone sensitive.The
opposite of overweight can be thin slim or skinny.

Light yellowish hair can be describe as blonde. But you can also call a person who has that kind kind of hair blonde.(This means blonde can be used as a noun or an adjective.) A person with dark hair can be called a redhead.

<H6>Besides what color someone's hair is you can say there are short-haired or long-haired.You can say they have curly staright or wavy hair.Sometimes hair can 
also be frizzy which is when it looks puffy with small tight curls. If someone has  no hair at all on their head they are bald.</H6>

<H4>IF SOMEONE DRESSES WELL. THEY ARE SMARTLY DESSED OR THEY LOOK SMART. YOU CAN ALSO JUST SAY THEY ARE WELL-DRESSED.IF SOMEONE DRESSES
FASHIONALLY THEY ARE STYLISH OR TRENDY.IF SOMEONE HAS BAD TASTE IN CLOTHE.YOU CAN SAY THEY ARE UNFASHIONABLE.A LESS NICE WAY TO SAY THIS IS FRUMPY.<H4>

<H5>Many people have mannerisms that appear when they are feeling negative(bad) emotions.If someone feels nervous or impatient for example they might tap their fingers crack their knuckles bite their fingernails or chew the tips of their pencils.</H5>
